{"type":"message","id":"239283fc","parentId":"734bb685","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:18:28.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script is still running. Let me check its log while also reading the most recent pulse log from the previous run.","thinkingSignature":"e66a09134a8986f21533e0f5f6001326a45046fd016b47fbc589b77b8519060b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k5mw4rm1dk6n_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 011614.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k5mw4rm1dk6n_2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"log","sessionId":"sharp-dune","limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":402,"output":120,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12476,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774329504619}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c74d353","parentId":"239283fc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:18:28.959Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_k5mw4rm1dk6n_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 011614\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze where we are and what needs to be done:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - the insight is that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\r\n2. The hypothesis is that causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n3. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on pulse logs\r\n\r\nCurrent pulse is pulse_2026-03-24 011439.md.\r\n\r\nThe pending task is:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that \"Causal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\"\r\n\r\nSo I need to implement a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier. This is a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse log files\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant elements across pulses\r\n3. Measures classification accuracy\r\n4. Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit - I'll create a new Python script for the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is solid - causal structure IS invariant structure. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the concrete next step to validate this hypothesis by classifying pulse content into invariants vs variants.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier Python script that analyzes pulse logs, identifies invariant/variant patterns, measures classification accuracy, and predicts next-pulse content from invariants.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n================================================\r\nHypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nA compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_sections(content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract named sections from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current_section = \"header\"\r\n    sections[current_section] = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        if line.startswith('## ') or line.startswith('### '):\r\n            current_section = line.lstrip('#').strip().lower()\r\n            sections[current_section] = []\r\n        else:\r\n            sections.setdefault(current_section, []).append(line)\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\ndef tokenize_lines(sections):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract content lines per section for comparison.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = {}\r\n    for section, lines in sections.items():\r\n        content = ' '.join(lines)\r\n        words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]+\\b', content.lower())\r\n        tokens[section] = set(words)\r\n    return tokens\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(tokens, all_tokens):\r\n    \"\"\"Score how 'invariant' a section's tokens are across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if not tokens:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    total_tokens = sum(len(t) for t in tokens.values())\r\n    if total_tokens == 0:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    invariant_count = 0\r\n    for section, words in tokens.items():\r\n        all_section = all_tokens.get(section, set())\r\n        # Token appears in this section across many pulses\r\n        appears_in = sum(1 for w in words if any(w in t.get(section, set()) for t in all_tokens))\r\n        invariant_count += appears_in\r\n    \r\n    return invariant_count / total_tokens\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariants(pulses_tokens, threshold=0.5):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify tokens as invariant (>threshold) vs variant (<threshold).\"\"\"\r\n    token_freq = Counter()\r\n    token_sections = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    for tokens in pulses_tokens:\r\n        for section, words in tokens.items():\r\n            for word in words:\r\n                token_freq[word] += 1\r\n                token_sections[word] += 1\r\n    \r\n    n_pulses = len(pulses_tokens)\r\n    invariants = set()\r\n    variants = set()\r\n    \r\n    for token, freq in token_freq.items():\r\n        ratio = freq / n_pulses\r\n        if ratio >= threshold:\r\n            invariants.add(token)\r\n        else:\r\n            variants.add(token)\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, current_tokens):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what next pulse will contain based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    predicted = []\r\n    \r\n    for section, words in current_tokens.items():\r\n        invariant_words = words & invariants\r\n        predicted.extend(invariant_words)\r\n    \r\n    return set(predicted)\r\n\r\ndef measure_prediction_accuracy(pulses_tokens, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Measure how well invariants predict next-pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    if len(pulses_tokens) < 2:\r\n        return 0.0, []\r\n    \r\n    correct = 0\r\n    total = 0\r\n    predictions_made = []\r\n    \r\n    for i in range(len(pulses_tokens) - 1):\r\n        current = pulses_tokens[i]\r\n        next_pulse = pulses_tokens[i + 1]\r\n        \r\n        predicted = predict_next_pulse(invariants, current)\r\n        \r\n        # Get all words from next pulse\r\n        next_words = set()\r\n        for section, words in next_pulse.items():\r\n            next_words.update(words)\r\n        \r\n        # True positives: predicted and actually appears\r\n        tp = len(predicted & next_words)\r\n        # False positives:\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:16:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329508957}}
